thread.title: CWC Volleyball keeps rolling

title: CWC Volleyball keeps rolling
text: Writer Posted Oct. 2, 2015 at 10:00 AM Updated Oct 2, 2015 at 10:32 AM Posted Oct. 2, 2015 at 10:00 AM Updated Oct 2, 2015 at 10:32 AM CARMI – The emotions weren’t as high in the gym as they were during Tuesday night’s “Pink Out” first place battle against Fairfield, but the CWC Lady Bulldogs remained undefeated in the BDC with a 25-19, 25-7 win over the Johnston City Lady Indians. The Lady Bulldogs jumped to an 8-3 the start in Game 1 and maintained a comfortable lead until the Lady Indians made their run and closed within 21-19. A tip at the net from Peighton Parks and an ace from Lixi Wheeler moved the score to 23-19. CWC scored the next two points to close the set. In Game 2 the Lady Bulldogs ran away early, causing Johnston City to call timeouts trailing 9-3 and 13-6. In this game CWC was very effective in tipping the ball over the net rather than attempting tougher kill shots. The game ended 25-7 on an ace from Paige Winter. In the earlier games, the CWC freshmen won 25-9, 25-22 and the JV remained undefeated with a 25-11, 25-19 victory.   Writer Posted Oct. 2, 2015 at 10:00 AM Updated Oct 2, 2015 at 10:32 AM
